STEPS FOR YALLLL

Step 1: Install the Required Tools
    Download and install Node.js from nodejs.org (click the LTS version)

Step 2: Go Into the Project Folder
    bashcd Project-ikharus/media_flow

Step 3: Install Dependencies
    This installs all the packages the project needs (replaces the node_modules folder that wasn't pushed to GitHub [the files were too large so just install it again]):
    bashnpm install

Step 4: Create the .env.local File
    The .env.local file wasnt pushed to GitHub because it contains secret keys. 

    Create a new file inside media_flow called .env.local
    Paste the contents you send them which should be:

    NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your_key_here  (i pinned it in messenger)
    CLERK_SECRET_KEY=your_key_here

    NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=/sign-in
    NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=/sign-up
    NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_IN_URL=/dashboard
    NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_UP_URL=/dashboard

Step 5: Run the Project
    bashnpm run dev
    Then open the browser and go to http://localhost:3000

